== Overview ==
A ''kannagi'' represents the act of communicating with a ''[[yorishiro]]'' of a ''[[kami]]'', or a [[Spirit possession|possession]] of a ''kami'', or a person who serves in that role.

[[Minakata Kumagusu|Kumagusu Minakata]], in his book ''Ichiko ni kansuru koto'', refers to ''[[miko]]'' serving shrines as ''kannagi'', and to [[Wandering Miko|wandering ''miko'']] as ''miko''.

